article.description: — Dillon Jones scored 29 points and grabbed 13 rebounds as Weber State beat Montana State 86-64 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Dillon Jones scores 29 points and grabs 13 rebounds, leads Weber State over Montana State 86-64
article.linkText: Dillon Jones scores 29 points and grabs 13 rebounds, leads Weber State over Montana State 86-64
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- — Dillon Jones scored 29 points and grabbed 13 rebounds as Weber State beat Montana State 86-64 on Saturday night. Jones also added six assists and four steals for the Wildcats (9-4, 2-0 Big Sky Conference). Steven Verplancken Jr. scored 14 points, and Dyson Koehler and Alex Tew added 12 apiece. Eddie Turner III led the way for the Bobcats (6-7, 1-1) with 18 points, four assists and two steals. Brandon Walker added 17 points for Montana State. Tyler Patterson also recorded 14 points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
